kyle stephan the clayman institute for gender research skip to main content standford university the clayman institute for gender research the clayman institute for gender research home programs news strategic focus events about research fellowships library media center gender news no news found events no events found you are here home people kyle stephan kyle stephan graduate art curator kyle stephan is the 2011 12 curator for the art at the institute program at the michelle r clayman institute for gender research a doctoral student in the department of art and art history her research interests include modern and contemporary art from latin america the aesthetics of pan americanism and intersections of art and technology including kinetic art and expanded cinema movements prior to beginning doctoral work at stanford stephan was a curator and media producer she created exhibitions for numerous cultural organizations including the sao paulo museum of modern art los angeles redcat theatre at the walt disney concert hall san francisco cinematheque and the british film institute where she worked as a film programmer from 2005 2010 stephan is also the producer of women art revolution a documentary film about the cultural social and artistic impact of the feminist art movement in the united states war screened at international film festivals such as the sundance toronto and berlin international film festivals and received its us theatrical release with zeitgeist films stephan has also successfully developed and collaborated on numerous interactive media art projects that have exhibited at venues such as villette numerique v2 rotterdam zkm isea and the new york digital salon donate make a donation social links facebook twitter youtube scribd contact serra house 589 capistrano way stanford ca 94305 8640 map 650 723 1994 gender email stanford edu
